Find the product of all integer divisors of $105$ that also divide $14$.  (Recall that the divisors of an integer may be positive or negative.)
inference:
The divisors of $105$ are $\pm1, \pm3, \pm5, \pm7, \pm15, \pm21, \pm35, \pm105$.  The divisors of $14$ are $\pm1, \pm2, \pm7, \pm14$.  So the divisors of $105$ that also divide $14$ are $\pm1, \pm7$.  Therefore, the product of all such divisors is $1 \times 7 = 7$.
Final Answer: \boxed{$7$}. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth: The factors of $105$ are $\pm 1, \pm 3, \pm 5, \pm 7, \pm 15, \pm 21, \pm 35, \pm 105$.  Of these, only $\pm 1$ and $\pm 7$ divide $14$.  Their product is $-7\cdot -1\cdot 1\cdot 7 = \boxed{49}$.
